      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "UP AND ALIVE (2) added to a long string of top-four results and made it two wins and a minor placing from her last three starts when she led from this barrier and dug deep to score by a head here last week. Can push forward again so looks tough to catch. EASTBRO CHRISSY (7) took her strike rate at this circuit and distance to 50 per cent when she led and got home by 3.7 metres last week. The driver has some work to do from this wide starting position but with even luck she could salute again. WALL STREET GIRL (1) drew wider and worked before going under by a neck as runner-up here last time out. The ace draw should see her competitive again. CAPTAINSHAVTIME NZ (4) is back from a let-up and her best efforts would measure up.",
